Implement a program to clcualte the free number of cups the user gets for a specified number of cups bought by the user. The user get 1 cup free for every 6 cups bought.

Input Format

number of cups

Constraints

no

Output Format

total number of coffee cups

Sample Input 0

6
Sample Output 0

7
Sample Input 1

8
Sample Output 1

9
Sample Input 2

10
Sample Output 2

11
Sample Input 3

12
Sample Output 3

14

import java.util.Scanner;

public class FreeCupsCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

        int cupsBought = scanner.nextInt();
        scanner.close();

        int freeCups = cupsBought / 6; // Calculate the number of free cups
        int totalCups = cupsBought + freeCups; // Calculate the total number of cups

        System.out.println(totalCups);
    }
}

 
